---
description: Asset Processor guardrails for image processing changes
alwaysApply: true
---

- Keep export preset definitions in one shared typed module.
- UI labels, API validation, resize width, and WebP quality must use the shared preset module.
- Validate API form fields at the route boundary.
- Return structured 400 or 415 responses for expected user input errors.
- Reserve Sentry exceptions for unexpected processing failures.
- Preserve useful Sentry context for server-side image processing.
- Add focused regression tests for new API behavior.
- Prefer the smallest coherent change.
- Do not add auth, persistence, queues, databases, or new dependencies unless explicitly requested.
